Sango: Turquie ayeke ngoro na a ngu ingo na mbage ti terê ti lo ota. Ngu ingo ti Égée na do, ngu ingo ti vuku na banga na ngu ingo ti Méditerranée mbongo. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Sango: Na to ngo nda ti bira ni, a la tambula na ndo ti ngu ingo, na yeke na yeke so si radar ni a to nda ti ga ngangu na ti ga mbîrîmbîrî, sa sous-marins a tonda ti linda na gbe ti ngu ti tene a bâa ala a pe 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Sango: Dutingo kpo na li ti oko ahoto ti banga ti Mecque, dutene ni ayeke yambe na tanga ti azo ni. 
English: The Holy City of Mecca was the first place where the Muslims were attacked by the Turks. The Turks attacked the Holy City of Mecca and the Muslims were defeated.
